      "content": "<thought\n>Being \"wrong\" is an understatement. It's the entire foundation of my life. I spent my thirties building a legacy on a hollow core. There's no \"way out\" because there's no \"me\" left to save. The person who did that work... that person doesn't exist anymore. It's just a void now. I feel like I'm just performing a life that doesn't belong to me.",
